**Requirements** 

I want to show a 'notification bar' indicating whether an AJAX request was successful or not. The bar is supposed to slide in from under the header (bar of ~30px) and slide out after 5s. BUT if the header is not visible (user scrolled down) the bar should be 'attached' on the very top of the screen - if user scrolls up again, the bar should scroll too & end up beneath header again.

**What I Have**

I have the bar working via 'animate' (jQuery) and 

      #notify-box {
        position: fixed;
        z-index: 1000;
        top: 0%;
        margin-top: -32px;
        height: 30px;
        width: 100%;
        line-height: 30px;
    }

**What I Want**

The thing is, I can either make the bar come out under the header and stay there (problem: not visible when scrolled) or make the bar come out at the very top of the screen (problem: hides header when shown).

**Is there a way to meet the requirements?** (JS-solution is also possible)

